x-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-main\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-rail\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-eyebrow\">Popular right now</span><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Tap to jump to the full answer.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip-row\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a popular-chip\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-question-circle\"></i>Which Virginia suburbs are most dog-friendly?</button></div></div><div role=\"list\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-accordion\"><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">01</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Which Virginia suburbs are most dog-friendly?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Arlington and Alexandria in Northern Virginia consistently rank among the most dog-friendly areas, with excellent park access, dog-friendly restaurants, and strong community culture.</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">cities</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Arlington and Alexandria in Northern Virginia consistently rank among the most dog-friendly areas, with excellent park access, dog-friendly restaurants, and strong community culture.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->cities</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article><article role=\"listitem\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-row \"><button type=\"button\" aria-expanded=\"false\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger\"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-main\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-index\">02</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><h4 class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Can I take my dog to Shenandoah National Park?</h4><p class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-preview\">Yes!</p></div></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-trigger-meta\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a category-chip\">Planning Your Visit</span><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-chevron-down\"></i></div></button><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel \"><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-answer\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:1rem;line-height:1.7\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Yes! Dogs are welcome on most trails and campgrounds in Shenandoah. They must be leashed (6 feet or shorter) at all times and are not permitted on certain trails due to wildlife considerations.</p></div><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a faq-panel-actions\"><span class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\">Category · <!-- -->Planning Your Visit</span><div class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a panel-buttons\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-hand-thumbs-up\"></i> Helpful</button><button type=\"button\" class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a\"><i class=\"jsx-ef56c8b56212c77a bi bi-share\"></i> Share</button></div></div></div></article></div></div></div></div></section><section class=\"state-section alt\"><div class=\"section-shell\"><div class=\"cta-band\"><div><h3>Help us expand <!-- -->Virginia<!-- --> coverage</h3><p>Submit your favorite spot and we’ll review it for inclusion in the directory.</p></div><div style